commit.message:
check for signal existence before registering in handler (#5)

Some signals are only defined on certain platforms.  For example,
SIGSTKFLT does not exist on sparc.  Use preprocessor macros to check for
signal's existence before registering signal handler for it.

Note that this is the same technique cpython uses:
https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/3.10/Modules/signalmodule.c#L1427

See: https://bugs.gentoo.org/807184

commit.message: fixed several compile warnings reported by recent gcc
restored ChangeLog from deleted debian/ folder and updated it
detachtty.1: better documented sending SIGTSTP or CTRL+Z to attachtty
config.h: set version to 11.0.0

detachtty.c: added command-line option "--version": shows version, copyright and license
detachtty.1: documented SIGQUIT and CTRL+Z
deleted debian/ folder: detachtty is no longer a native Debian program
added full GPL v2.0 to COPYING. added explicit copyright to all sources and headers
added COPYING. updated INSTALL and README with new maintainer and URLs
detachtty.c: added #include <pty.h> for forkpty() declaration
detachtty: compiling with #define NEED_SET_NOECHO forces -iecho mode to child tty
new file .gitignore
more tweaks to error messages
tweaked error messages a bit
detachtty: commented out call to set_noecho() until somebody points out a good reason for it

re-added Daniel Barlow's fixes for Makefile and EPIPE errors;
detachtty: refactored main()
detachtty: improved robustness of forking in background
fixed typo #warn -> #warning
attachtty: send window size to command running inside detachtty
set line-buffering to stdout and stderr - useful for log messages
added \r\n to logprintf() to avoid staircase effect
attachtty: added clean exit upon end-of-file while reading from socket or standard input
detachtty: do not pass pts_name[] to forkpty, as minimum buffer length cannot be determined
updated download url in README
updated README
attachtty: added support for timeout also on remote (ssh) sockets.
updated man page detachtty.1

attachtty: fixed support for CTRL+Z.
attachtty: when command is specified, terminate it with '\r' instead of '\n'
attachtty: added handling of suspend signal generated by CTRL+Z
